  "prompt": "I scored 72% in 10th and 88% in 12 can I be able to became ias officer?",
  "response": "Your academic scores in 10th and 12th grades do not determine your eligibility to become an IAS officer. The eligibility criteria for becoming an IAS officer are set by the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) in India. Here are the main requirements:\n\n1. **Educational Qualification**: You must have at least a bachelor's degree from a recognized university.\n\n2. **Age Limit**: Generally, candidates must be between 21 and 32 years of age. There are age relaxations for candidates belonging to specific categories (such as SC/ST, OBC, etc.).\n\n3. **Nationality**:\n   - You must be a citizen of India, or\n   - A subject of Nepal, or\n   - A subject of Bhutan, or\n   - A Tibetan refugee who came to India before January 1, 1962, with the intention of permanently settling in India, or\n   - A person of Indian origin who has migrated from Pakistan, Burma, Sri Lanka, East African countries of Kenya, Uganda, the United Republic of Tanzania, Zambia, Malawi, Zaire, Ethiopia and Vietnam with the intention of permanently settling in India.\n\nTo become an IAS officer, you need to clear the Civil Services Examination conducted by UPSC. The exam has three stages:\n1. **Preliminary Examination**: An objective-type exam.\n2. **Main Examination**: A written examination consisting of essay-type questions.\n3. **Interview/Personality Test**: An interview to assess your personality and suitability for a career in civil services.\n\nYour scores in 10th and 12th grades will not affect your ability to prepare for and succeed in the UPSC exams. Focus on developing a strong understanding of current affairs, history, polity, economics, and other relevant subjects. Good preparation, dedication, and consistent effort are critical to clearing the UPSC exams and becoming an IAS officer.",
